    <updated>2015-06-29T13:40:14-06:00</updated>
    <id>http://dubbs.github.io/blog/2015/06/29/installing-solr-on-centos-6</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2>Install Java</h2>

<pre><code class="bash"># install java-1.7.0-openjdk
sudo yum -y install java-1.7.0-openjdk
</code></pre>

<h2>Install Solr 5</h2>

<pre><code class="bash"># http://lucene.apache.org/solr/downloads.html
wget http://archive.apache.org/dist/lucene/solr/5.0.0/solr-5.0.0.tgz
tar zxf solr-5.0.0.tgz
cd solr-5.0.0/
bin/solr start
bin/solr create -c demo
</code></pre>
